If you are using Nuxt they expect a `store/index.js` to create a store and the format should be like:

```js
export const state = () =&gt; ({
  counter: 0
})

export const mutations = {
  increment (state) {
    state.counter++
  }
}
```

As you are creating a `store/store.js` file, that will be treated as a module and might not work as you expect. I strongly recommend to create a `store/index.js` and follow the docs from [Nuxt][1].


  [1]: https://nuxtjs.org/guide/vuex-store#activate-the-store

